# Tutorial: Correct Segmentation

<img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="">

![](./49.jpg?raw=true "Optional Title")

Segmentation is rarely perfect ! But you can easily fix errors. To do so, click on the correction tab

<img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="">

![](./50.jpg?raw=true "Optional Title")

Left click over the image window to draw a new contact<ul><li>the drawn bond should intersect two existing contacts to be taken into account</li><li>the drawn contact may extend inside adjacent cells, extra pixels will be removed automatically</li></ul>Use right click/Cmd+click to remove pixels from the image<ul><li>Removing just one pixel from a contact is sufficient to remove the entire contact</li></ul>Press 'Enter' or 'Shift+Enter' when you are done drawing or removing contacts to update the segmentation

<img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt=""><img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="">

![](./51.jpg?raw=true "Optional Title")

The Spinner controls the size of the TA pen (e.g. you can make it bigger to remove a lot of cells at the same time) and the green button applies the cell corrections

<img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="">

![](./52.jpg?raw=true "Optional Title")

Click on the 'PostProcess' Tab

<img align="top" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="">

![](./53.jpg?raw=true "Optional Title")

Press the finish all button to generate TA default output files and databases
- TA saved the Watershed segmentation mask in the file named 'handCorrection.tif'
- TA saves the local cell identity in the file named 'cell_identity.tif'
- TA saves the local contact identity in the file named 'boundaryPlotter.tif'
- TA saves all inforamtions extracted from cells in the 'TA.db' files (area, perimeter, polarity, cell elongation, cell orientation, ...)
